        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 1:50PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 150 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northeast of Hendersonville, or near Chimney Rock Village,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Lure, Old Fort, Chimney Rock Village, Chimney Rock State Park,
Bat Cave, Fairview In Buncombe County, Shingle Hollow, and Gerton.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
